The Emir of Gwandu and Chairman, Kebbi State Council of Chiefs, Alhaji Muhammadu Iliyasu Bashar, has advised parents to guide their children on religious values and use the lessons from the Ramadan to forgive one another as a family. He made the call after the two rakaat prayers presided over by Imam Ahmad Rufai at the Eid praying ground in Birnin Kebbi yesterday. He said parents have a big role to play in child upbringing while children are expected to respect their parents and leaders. The emir also prayed for bumper harvest, peace and tranquility in the country while congratulating the Muslim ummah on the Sallah celebration.